The paper discusses the use of Business Process Management (BPM) tools and practices, which are typically used in enterprise applications. This suggests that the paper may belong to the category of Computer Science and Information Technology (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of blockchains as a shared ledger for parties collaborating on a process, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms and deep learning models suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the development and monitoring of business processes, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
